THE BEATLES - Don't Let Me Wait Too Long
Imagine if The Beatles had not disbanded and, after having released a double vinyl LP in 1971 (That Would Be Something), they went on to release another double vinyl LP in 1975 called Don't Let Me Wait Too Long.  Using 1972-1975 solo material this attempts to create a 1975 Beatles album that fits on a single CD or double vinyl LP.
